01:12:57,431 --> 01:13:01,014
Now, I know you did not go in there
to tell this guy something he already knew.

1164
01:13:01,102 --> 01:13:02,430
Talk to me.

1165
01:13:02,978 --> 01:13:04,058
Look, Detective.

1166
01:13:04,146 --> 01:13:06,637
Our arrangement doesn't include me
giving you a detailed explanation.

1167
01:13:06,732 --> 01:13:08,523
I say it does, okay?

1168
01:13:08,859 --> 01:13:10,270
Okay, you don't own me.

1169
01:13:10,361 --> 01:13:13,527
This cheque-cashing thing, this coke bust,
I can face that on my own.

1170
01:13:13,614 --> 01:13:16,152
I know what I did and what I didn't do.

1171
01:13:16,242 --> 01:13:18,697
- Talk to me.
- Off the record?

1172
01:13:18,786 --> 01:13:22,700
"Off the..." Everything about you
is off the record. Just talk to me.

1173
01:13:23,040 --> 01:13:25,365
- Well, I gave him an incentive.
- Okay.

1174
01:13:25,501 --> 01:13:29,545
- Did he go for it?
- No. But I'd say he's considering it.

1175
01:13:30,881 --> 01:13:32,541
He's smart, isn't he?

1176
01:13:32,800 --> 01:13:34,507
- He thinks he is.
- Yeah.

1177
01:13:35,010 --> 01:13:37,679
One of your types, like the Ivy League type?

1178
01:13:38,222 --> 01:13:40,891
- Clearly well educated.
- That's what I'm talking about.

1179
01:13:40,974 --> 01:13:43,050
That's exactly what I'm talking about.

1180
01:13:43,143 --> 01:13:47,093
You talk like him, so think like him.
What do you think he's gonna do?

1181
01:13:48,774 --> 01:13:51,181
- Well, he's not gonna kill anyone.
- How do you know?

1182
01:13:51,276 --> 01:13:54,028
- Because he's not a murderer.
- How do you know?

1183
01:13:54,112 --> 01:13:56,271
I got news for you.
Most of the guys up in Sing Sing

1184
01:13:56,364 --> 01:13:58,072
weren't murderers
until they killed somebody.

1185
01:13:58,158 --> 01:14:02,156
You never know what a person will do
until you push him into a corner.

1186
01:14:02,412 --> 01:14:04,820
But it doesn't seem
like you've pushed him into a corner.

1187
01:14:04,915 --> 01:14:08,284
It doesn't, does it?
Seems more like he chose the corner.

1188
01:14:09,920 --> 01:14:11,200
You're right.

1189
01:14:12,213 --> 01:14:13,756
So, you through?

1190
01:14:14,799 --> 01:14:17,088
- I guess. Are you saying I'm dismissed?
- Yes, I am.

1191
01:14:17,177 --> 01:14:19,798
You got a card, in case I need to call you?

1192
01:14:20,346 --> 01:14:23,264
Please don't take this personally, but no.

1193
01:14:23,433 --> 01:14:25,010
I don't think you can afford me.

1194
01:14:25,101 --> 01:14:29,051
Well, don't take this personally, Miss White.
Kiss my black ass, okay?

1195
01:14:29,230 --> 01:14:33,442
Careful, Detective Frazier.
My bite's much worse than my bark.

1196
01:14:39,449 --> 01:14:41,525
- So, how old are you, Brian?
- Eight and three-quarters.

1197
01:14:41,617 --> 01:14:44,191
Eight and three-quarters. Big boy.

1198
01:14:45,413 --> 01:14:47,536
- Were you scared in there?
- No.

1199
01:14:47,623 --> 01:14:50,293
- No? Not at all, huh?
- Nope. I'm from Brooklyn.

1200
01:14:50,376 --> 01:14:51,954
You're from Brooklyn, huh? I understand.

1201
01:14:52,044 --> 01:14:53,752
- Guns don't scare me.
- They don't scare you?

1202
01:14:53,838 --> 01:14:55,249
- Brave, too, huh?
- Yeah.

1203
01:14:55,339 --> 01:14:58,791
So the guys that had the guns,
do you remember them saying anything?

1204
01:14:58,885 --> 01:15:00,758
- Yeah.
- What'd they say?

1205
01:15:00,845 --> 01:15:02,339
They asked me about my game.

1206
01:15:02,430 --> 01:15:05,099
- Who did?
- The guy that robbed the bank. Duh.

1207
01:15:05,766 --> 01:15:07,474
Son, be respectful.

1208
01:15:07,560 --> 01:15:10,311
Okay, Brooklyn.
But it... Was he the one in charge?

1209
01:15:10,396 --> 01:15:11,475
- Uh-huh.
- Okay.

1210
01:15:11,772 --> 01:15:14,394
And you don't remember anything else?

1211
01:15:14,567 --> 01:15:16,109
He was kind of tall.

1212
01:15:16,902 --> 01:15:18,100
He had a mask.

1213
01:15:18,195 --> 01:15:22,145
Brian, you think you can recognise him
in any of these pictures?

1214
01:15:23,117 --> 01:15:25,406
Take your time. Have a good look.

1215
01:15:25,953 --> 01:15:28,658
Let's keep that over there. Just take a look.

1216
01:15:35,170 --> 01:15:38,374
- With the mask, they look all the same.
- It's true.

1217
01:15:40,134 --> 01:15:43,088
With the mask, they all look the same.
That's right, Brian.

1218
01:15:43,178 --> 01:15:46,512
Attempted robbery. Liquor store.

1219
01:15:46,807 --> 01:15:50,342
Well, this was a real step up
for a small-timer like you, huh?

1220
01:15:50,978 --> 01:15:52,804
I got to hand it to you, Pablo.

1221
01:15:52,896 --> 01:15:56,431
First of all, it's Paul. Not Pablo, okay?

1222
01:15:56,650 --> 01:15:57,729
Excuse me.

1223
01:15:58,902 --> 01:16:00,729
- You want some gum?
- No.

1224
01:16:01,530 --> 01:16:03,190
And second, I didn't do it, all right?

1225
01:16:03,281 --> 01:16:05,772
What? I made a few mistakes
when I was a kid.

1226
01:16:05,867 --> 01:16:09,319
I was out with some friends
and they held up a liquor store.

1227
01:16:10,247 --> 01:16:12,073
What was I supposed to do?

1228
01:16:13,875 --> 01:16:16,034
Where'd you grow up, you Wassa Wassa,
Park Avenue?

1229
01:16:16,127 --> 01:16:18,665
- What's that? Wassa what? What'd you say?
- Wassa Wassa.

1230
01:16:18,755 --> 01:16:19,870
(SPEAKING IN SPANISH)

1231
01:16:19,965 --> 01:16:22,206
You know, a person
that don't come to your neighbourhood.

1232
01:16:22,300 --> 01:16:24,589
How do you say "Rikers Island" in Spanish?

1233
01:16:24,678 --> 01:16:26,255
What about these two?

1234
01:16:26,596 --> 01:16:28,055
That ring a bell?

1235
01:16:28,306 --> 01:16:30,513
These two? No.

1236
01:16:30,600 --> 01:16:31,845
- Nothing?
- Nothing.

1237
01:16:31,935 --> 01:16:33,346
Don't they look suspicious to you?

1238
01:16:33,436 --> 01:16:36,936
I mean, I would think that you would
want to know who they are.

1239
01:16:37,023 --> 01:16:38,186
No.

1240
01:16:38,274 --> 01:16:39,934
- Well, thank you very much.
- Thank you.

1241
01:16:40,026 --> 01:16:42,731
Hey, just out of curiosity
do you know anything about diamonds?

1242
01:16:42,820 --> 01:16:44,897
A bit. What do you need?

1243
01:16:44,989 --> 01:16:47,231
What do you think a guy like me
should pay for a diamond ring?

1244
01:16:47,325 --> 01:16:49,282
Depends. How many carats?

1245
01:16:49,369 --> 01:16:51,361
If you'd like, I could give you
my nephew's number.

1246
01:16:51,454 --> 01:16:52,829
- Okay.
- You'll get a very good deal.

1247
01:16:52,914 --> 01:16:54,906
What do you have on underneath?

1248
01:16:55,083 --> 01:16:57,289
- Excuse me?
- Underneath your painter's coat?

1249
01:16:57,377 --> 01:16:59,583
- What do you have on underneath?
- Clothing.

1250
01:16:59,670 --> 01:17:01,746
Could you show us, please?

1251
01:17:06,010 --> 01:17:08,050
You see, there's just you
and one other woman

1252
01:17:08,137 --> 01:17:10,711
that fit the physical description
of the female suspect.

1253
01:17:10,806 --> 01:17:12,005
What's that?

1254
01:17:13,434 --> 01:17:16,720
It's your height, your age, and your...

1255
01:17:17,605 --> 01:17:18,980
Your cup size.

1256
01:17:19,065 --> 01:17:22,516
So, I violated Section 34 double-D?

1257
01:17:22,610 --> 01:17:24,519
That's what you're telling me?

1258
01:17:28,157 --> 01:17:31,407
How dumb do these morons have to be
to think they're gonna get a plane?

1259
01:17:31,494 --> 01:17:32,608
This guy's no moron.

1260
01:17:32,703 --> 01:17:35,455
I don't just mean him. Any hostage taker.

1261
01:17:36,832 --> 01:17:39,453
Those ragheads at the Munich Olympics.

1262
01:17:39,919 --> 01:17:41,543
Who the fuck ever got a plane?

1263
01:17:41,629 --> 01:17:44,298
Shit, and these days?
This guy doesn't know that?

1264
01:17:44,381 --> 01:17:45,544
REPORTER: (ON TV) The area is flooded

1265
01:17:45,633 --> 01:17:48,040
with law enforcement right now.
Snipers are on rooftops...

1266
01:17:48,135 --> 01:17:49,415
What you doing there, Keith?

1267
01:17:49,511 --> 01:17:51,255
He wants a plane.
I'm gonna give him a plane.

1268
01:17:51,346 --> 01:17:54,098
- What happened to playing it by the book?
- That's what's bugging me.

1269
01:17:54,183 --> 01:17:59,010
It's like the other team read the book, too,
and they know exactly what we're gonna do.

1270
01:18:01,481 --> 01:18:04,981
This whole time,
we're trying to stall him, right?

1271
01:18:05,068 --> 01:18:06,860
Wrong. They're the ones that are stalling.

1272
01:18:06,945 --> 01:18:09,353
Think about it.
The bullshit questions, the Albanian thing...

1273
01:18:09,448 --> 01:18:10,942
So, you're saying he what?

1274
01:18:11,033 --> 01:18:14,651
I'm saying that he wants
to give us more time. He makes demands.

1275
01:18:14,786 --> 01:18:18,036
He gives us deadlines. We stall.
Then he gives us more time.

1276
01:18:18,123 --> 01:18:19,498
I don't think he's in a rush.

1277
01:18:19,583 --> 01:18:21,908
- Why?
- That's what I'm gonna find out.

1278
01:18:25,839 --> 01:18:27,582
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

1279
01:18:43,064 --> 01:18:44,606
- Yeah.
- Your plane is ready.

1280
01:18:44,691 --> 01:18:45,853
Is that a fact?

1281
01:18:45,942 --> 01:18:48,398
That's a fact, but I'm gonna need something
from you first.

1282
01:18:48,486 --> 01:18:51,571
I'm gonna need to come in there
and make sure the hostages are okay.

1283
01:18:51,656 --> 01:18:53,364
You'll see them when they get on the bus.

1284
01:18:53,449 --> 01:18:56,984
I just need to make sure
you're not leaving any bodies behind.

1285
01:18:59,330 --> 01:19:01,074
Meet me at the front door.

1286
01:19:07,130 --> 01:19:10,878
- What the hell just happened?
- You got to be crazy to go in there.

1287
01:20:00,474 --> 01:20:01,802
DALTON: Down the stairs.

1288
01:20:10,150 --> 01:20:11,977
- Gum?
- Excuse me?

1289
01:20:12,236 --> 01:20:15,236
- Would you like some gum?
- No, thank you.

1290
01:20:28,335 --> 01:20:30,126
(WOMAN WHIMPERING)

1291
01:21:04,621 --> 01:21:06,115
Let me take the kid.

1292
01:21:07,832 --> 01:21:08,947
No.

1293
01:21:09,834 --> 01:21:10,997
Any more?

1294
01:21:11,669 --> 01:21:13,792
There are some who misbehaved.

1295
01:21:18,551 --> 01:21:19,749
(ALL YELLING)

1296
01:21:19,844 --> 01:21:21,504
Please help me!

1297
01:21:22,388 --> 01:21:23,764
Please help us!

1298
01:21:23,848 --> 01:21:26,304
Please help us! Please!

1299
01:21:26,976 --> 01:21:29,099
We're gonna get you all out of here.

1300
01:21:29,187 --> 01:21:30,930
I promise you.

1301
01:21:31,731 --> 01:21:32,929
Tour is over.

1302
01:21:41,407 --> 01:21:44,823
- Can I ask you a question?
- There is nothing to talk about.

1303
01:21:45,453 --> 01:21:47,161
What were you planning on doing

1304
01:21:47,246 --> 01:21:50,164
if you actually got
the plane and the pilots, huh?

1305
01:21:50,416 --> 01:21:53,168
- Excuse me?
- You don't want a plane. You never did.

1306
01:21:53,252 --> 01:21:56,538
Who ever heard of bank robbers
escaping on a plane with 50 hostages?

1307
01:21:56,630 --> 01:22:00,165
You saw Dog Day Afternoon. You're stalling.
Why? I don't know.

1308
01:22:00,926 --> 01:22:03,382
What's the matter?
You can't get into the safe?

1309
01:22:03,470 --> 01:22:05,013
Perhaps.

1310
01:22:05,931 --> 01:22:07,390
There's two ways out of this.

1311
01:22:07,474 --> 01:22:11,389
The easy way, we walk out the front door
together, or the hard boys cut the power,

1312
01:22:11,478 --> 01:22:14,313
hit you with the tear gas,
and come in strong through the glass.

1313
01:22:14,398 --> 01:22:17,352
It's your choice. You don't want that.
I don't want that.

1314
01:22:17,443 --> 01:22:19,649
And, you know, they'd like to do it tonight.

1315
01:22:19,736 --> 01:22:21,563
You got night vision?

1316
01:22:22,072 --> 01:22:24,741
- You got gas masks?
- Maybe.

1317
01:22:25,951 --> 01:22:28,442
- I'm this close to ordering it.
- Let's cut the crap.

1318
01:22:28,537 --> 01:22:31,538
First, you don't order an assault
when no hostages have been killed

1319
01:22:31,623 --> 01:22:33,117
and there's no immediate threat.

1320
01:22:33,208 --> 01:22:36,292
Second, if it ends that way,
whatever happens,

1321
01:22:36,378 --> 01:22:38,038
you don't get to be the hero.

1322
01:22:38,130 --> 01:22:40,288
You want to bullshit me, try harder.

1323
01:22:41,091 --> 01:22:42,253
Let's go.

1324
01:22:44,177 --> 01:22:45,340
Okay.

1325
01:22:52,853 --> 01:22:55,806
I tell you what. My ass is covered, sport.

1326
01:22:55,897 --> 01:22:58,519
But I would not get too comfortable
in here if I were you.

1327
01:22:58,608 --> 01:23:01,277
No? I got the cable guy
coming on Wednesday.

1328
01:23:01,903 --> 01:23:04,608
- Why don't you just walk out the door?
- I will.

1329
01:23:06,366 --> 01:23:09,569
I'm gonna walk out of that door
when I'm good and ready.

1330
01:23:09,828 --> 01:23:11,820
Can I get you to do that today?

1331
01:23:13,581 --> 01:23:14,910
I didn't think so.

1332
01:23:14,999 --> 01:23:16,280
Any other proposals?

1333
01:23:16,376 --> 01:23:18,582
Oh, please. Do not say "proposals."

1334
01:23:18,670 --> 01:23:21,421
My girlfriend, she wants a proposal from me.

1335
01:23:21,506 --> 01:23:25,171
- You think you're too young to get married?
- No, I'm not too young. Too broke.

1336
01:23:25,260 --> 01:23:27,501
Maybe I should rob a bank.

1337
01:23:28,554 --> 01:23:30,262
You love each other?

1338
01:23:30,807 --> 01:23:32,633
Yeah. Yeah, we do.

1339
01:23:32,767 --> 01:23:34,925
Then money shouldn't really matter.

1340
01:23:35,520 --> 01:23:37,144
Thank you, bank robber.

1341
01:23:37,522 --> 01:23:40,772
I'm just saying money can't buy love.

1342
01:23:42,527 --> 01:23:45,196
Thank you very much. I'm...

1343
01:23:46,614 --> 01:23:48,856
I'm learning so much today, you know?

1344
01:23:49,617 --> 01:23:52,452
Look, why don't we go across
the street to the Killarney Rose, huh?

1345
01:23:52,536 --> 01:23:54,363
Forget about
this dangerous hostage situation.

1346
01:23:54,455 --> 01:23:56,993
- L'll buy you a beer. My treat.
- Thanks, Detective,

1347
01:23:57,083 --> 01:24:00,202
but I'm trying to stay away from bars,
if you know what I mean.

1348
01:24:00,294 --> 01:24:04,339
Well, if you change your mind
there's still a standing offer, all right?

1349
01:24:09,553 --> 01:24:11,712
Cellblock or the graveyard?

1350
01:24:11,805 --> 01:24:13,597
Prison whites or a toe tag?

1351
01:24:13,682 --> 01:24:17,134
- Make up your mind. Tick tock, tick tock.
- Hey! Hey!

1352
01:24:18,062 --> 01:24:19,342
We done?

1353
01:24:22,107 --> 01:24:24,230
You just crossed the fucking line!

1354
01:24:26,028 --> 01:24:28,234
Buses, Kojak, parked outside.

1355
01:24:28,739 --> 01:24:30,399
You think I'm bluffing?

1356
01:24:31,575 --> 01:24:33,900
You roll the dice and see what happens.

1357
01:24:42,920 --> 01:24:44,912
COP: All right. Now get the bunker up.

1358
01:24:45,005 --> 01:24:46,997
- So, what's up?
- Got him right where I want him.

1359
01:24:47,090 --> 01:24:48,253
Yeah? Where's that?

1360
01:24:48,342 --> 01:24:51,757
Right behind me with my pants
around my ankles, but it's a start.

1361
01:24:51,845 --> 01:24:53,256
Jesus Christ.

1362
01:25:08,069 --> 01:25:09,398
- What the fuck, man?
- How long?

1363
01:25:09,487 --> 01:25:10,946
- He got the drop on you!
- Two.

1364
01:25:11,031 --> 01:25:12,406
- How long?
- What if he saw your face?

1365
01:25:12,490 --> 01:25:13,819
- Two.
- What if I didn't have my gun?

1366
01:25:13,908 --> 01:25:15,652
Two, maybe three hours.

1367
01:25:15,744 --> 01:25:18,910
You know, you're letting this cop
get too fucking close.

1368
01:25:22,000 --> 01:25:23,198
What happened?

1369
01:25:23,293 --> 01:25:25,166
I gave him every excuse
to blow my brains out.

1370
01:25:25,295 --> 01:25:26,409
Yeah.

1371
01:25:26,504 --> 01:25:29,589
He doesn't bite. Why? He ain't the type.

1372
01:25:29,674 --> 01:25:32,130
Let's just step back
and think about this for a second.

1373
01:25:32,218 --> 01:25:35,753
We know that they planned this whole thing.
The tape, the cameras, the costumes.

1374
01:25:35,847 --> 01:25:38,135
There was a game plan,
but it never included aeroplanes.

1375
01:25:38,224 --> 01:25:40,893
He's up to something but it ain't violence.

1376
01:25:40,977 --> 01:25:42,685
(TELEPHONE RINGING)

1377
01:25:44,897 --> 01:25:47,471
FRAZIER: I'm listening.
DALTON: How's the reception?

1378
01:25:47,859 --> 01:25:50,266
- Excuse me?
- The camera on the truck.

1379
01:25:50,695 --> 01:25:53,316
Give me a close-up
on the second-floor window.

1380
01:25:54,031 --> 01:25:55,989
- Rourke?
- I'm on it, I'm on it.

1381
01:26:07,503 --> 01:26:09,994
No, no, no, no, no, no! Fuck!

1382
01:26:10,089 --> 01:26:11,417
Oh, shit.

1383
01:26:15,010 --> 01:26:17,846
Keith! Keith! Keith!

1384
01:26:17,930 --> 01:26:19,590
(ALL YELLING)

1385
01:26:24,144 --> 01:26:26,517
What are you doing?
What the fuck are you doing?

1386
01:26:26,605 --> 01:26:28,681
You mean beyond the obvious?

1387
01:26:28,857 --> 01:26:31,313
That's what I mean.
Come on, this ain't no bank robbery!

1388
01:26:31,402 --> 01:26:34,272
This is your fault.
I told you to get the buses.

1389
01:26:34,363 --> 01:26:37,779
Fuck you! I didn't kill anybody.

1390
01:26:39,868 --> 01:26:42,573
I got 50 more people in here.
You fuck with me again,

1391
01:26:42,663 --> 01:26:44,821
l'll give you two
of the longest days of your life.

1392
01:26:44,915 --> 01:26:49,209
All right, look, just tell me what
it is you really want and l'll get it for you.

1393
01:26:49,294 --> 01:26:52,081
- I promise.
- I've told you. Two buses, a plane.

1394
01:26:52,172 --> 01:26:54,877
